Merkel Asked for China for Artist Ai’s Release, Spiegel Reports

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-04-16T16:11:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/merkel-asked-for-china-for-artist-ai-s-release-spiegel-reports.html
     April 16 (Bloomberg) --German Chancellor  Angela Merkel 
personally asked the Chinese government to release Ai Weiwei, an
artist who was arrested in Beijing two weeks ago, Der  Spiegel 
reported.  The human rights committee of the Bundestag also wrote to
the Chinese President Hu Jintao on Ai’s behalf, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in Frankfurt at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 